messages.message: Been seeing this on prod and cannot determine what causes it. Seems all my latest fields i have created will randomly get this error and have to flip back and forth between files or reopen up the prompt to get it to go away
@joshbronko does this happen with any specific document/project? Or does it happen completely randomly?
and are you seeing anything in the console/network tab? I’m currently unable to reproduce this on prod
keep your volume low as my dog started to bark haha :slightly_smiling_face:
before it wouldnt say heavy load error
I need admin access to access your project cc @Eric Han @Jessica . @joshbronko would be great to get a har file for this in the meantime or see if there are any errors being logged to the console
I think I can reproduce this… seems like it might be from having too many fields. The error I’m getting from the extraction is `too many requests`
dont steal my session cookie now :slightly_smiling_face:

thanks. Confirmed that this is the same thing I’m seeing. I’m not sure that we place limits on the number of fields you can create and if you have too many and we try to extract them all it looks like the backend restricts this
@Jessica what is a good resolution here? Do we limit the number of fields the user can create? Or do we need to change how fire off the network requests  to extract fields?
It might make sense to do bulk extraction if a user has more than x fields
@Arjun can you send this to <#C04PFH9DYF7|>? Since this is an error coming back from OpenAI. Let's not try to design the frontend behavior around this
sure I’ll send in that channel. I’m not sure that this is necessarily an OpenAI error or if our backend is doing some kind of limiting
Hmm yeah it might be our limiting, but regardless we should fix that at that level
